::Prowl::

Prowl shruggs as Iron Raptor asks her questions, still looking at 
her. He didn't know too well either, but he had an idea on how this 
happened.

An idea pops into his mind. If they could sense each other's 
thoughts, then.....

"I don't know," he thinks at her, wondering if she'd be able to hear 
it, "But I'm guessing that theses are the side effects of the merge."




--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, "Megan Solmonson" <tmrattrap@h...> wrote:
> 
> 
> * Iron Raptor had a hunch that something was happening here that 
she 
> couldn't even begin to try and work out, but she also had an idea 
that Prowl 
> was going through the same thing as she was. So at least she 
wouldn't have 
> to figure all of this out on her own.
> Besides, she also was sure that Prowl knew a hell of a lot more 
then she did 
> about all this, and maybe could fill her in on a few things to help 
her 
> understand.
> 
> But Iron Raptor watched him nod after she spoke his name, not use 
to this 
> body and its speaking abilities.
> Though, as she watched him lean closer to her, she suddenly 
felt...felt that 
> everything would be all right. Even though it all seemed so strange.
> 
> The sound of Prowls voice answering her relaxed what tensions she 
had, her 
> eyes following him as he kneeled down beside her.
> Watching Prowl as he ran his hand through her hair, just sitting 
and 
> watching.
> So much had happened, and she was only catching up. Tilting her 
head towards 
> Prowls hand, her mind asking a million questions.
> But she only spoke two.*
> 
> " What are we, and how did this happen?"
> 
> 
>
